                    <div class="card my-3">
                        <h5 id="account" class="card-header fs-2 text-center">Your Account</h5>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title fs-3">Introduction to Your Account</h5>
                            <p class="card-text fs-5">Cheap Carts allows users to make changes to their account. People can change their password and zip code. Users can also delete their account if needed.</p>

                            <hr>

                            <h5 class="card-title fs-3">Getting to the Account Page</h5>
                            <p class="card-text fs-5">In order to reach the <a href="/account" class="guide-link text-Cambridge link-underline link-underline-opacity-0">Account</a> page (when signed in) users can click their name and greeting in the navigation bar to access the dropdown menu and click on <a href="/account" class="guide-link text-Cambridge link-underline link-underline-opacity-0">"Account."</a>

                            They could also scroll down to the footer and click <a href="/account" class="guide-link text-Cambridge link-underline link-underline-opacity-0">"Settings"</a> underneath the “My Account” section.
                            </p>

                            <hr>

                            <h5 class="card-title fs-3">Account Information</h5>
                            <p class="card-text fs-5">The “Account Information” section contains the user’s username and zip code.</p>
                            
                            <p class="card-text fs-5 fw-bold">This is what the Account Information section looks like:</p>

                            <img class="border mb-2" src="/static/other_images/accountinfo.png" alt="The Account Information section of the account page" width="500px">

                            <hr>

                            <h5 class="card-title fs-3">Changing Password</h5>
                            <p class="card-text fs-5">In order for a user to change their passwords all they need to do is go to the “Change Password” section, enter their current password, new password, confirm their new password, and click the “Change Password” button.</p>

                            <p class="card-text fs-5 fw-bold">This is what the Change Password section looks like:</p>

                            <img class="border mb-2" src="/static/other_images/changepassword.png" alt="The Change Password section of the account page" width="500px">

                            <p class="card-text fs-5">Users must ensure that the new password matches across both fields and the new password must be longer than 8 characters. </p>

                            <p class="card-text fs-5">You can also toggle the visibility of password fields by pressing the “eyeball” button.</p>

                            <p class="card-text fs-5 fw-bold">This is what the Show and Hide Password buttons looks like:</p>

                            <button id="show_new_password_btn" class="btn btn-outline-dark" type="button">
